Bring a #medium-sized pan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Trim the @green beans{150%g} and chop into thirds.

Halve the @red chilli{1/2}(halved lengthways, deseeded and thinly sliced), trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

When the water is boiling, add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back into the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Heat a #large frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @sesame seeds{15%g} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch the sesame seeds like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once toasted, transfer to a #bowl{} (make sure you get them all) and set aside.

Pop your pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

When hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and stir-fry until golden on the outside, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Stir in the onion and green beans. Cook with the chicken until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @teriyaki sauce{150%g} to the pan along with the @water{50%ml} for the sauce.

Stir everything together and simmer until the sauce is sticky, the beans are tender and the chicken is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Taste the sauce and add @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch} if needed.

Stir in the sesame seeds and add a splash of water if it needs loosening.

Fluff up the rice and serve with the teriyaki chicken on top.

Sprinkle over the spring onion and chilli. Enjoy!

> Add less chilli if you don't like heat.

> STEP 4 MOD: If you've chosen to get chicken breast instead of chicken thigh, cook the recipe in the same way the instructions tell you to cook the chicken thigh.